This paper discusses a traffic analysis attack against HTTPS deployments, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack involves analyzing network traffic, which also relates to network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the exposure of personal details, which could fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses evaluation methodology and the effectiveness of defenses, which could fall under the categories of systems and information theory (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively.
